SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 655
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Wade Davies for his
honorable and astute service to the people of
Tennessee as the 2025-2026 President of the
Tennessee Association of Criminal Defense
Lawyers.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
attorneys who have distinguished themselves as professional leaders of whom we can all be
proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy individual is Wade Davies of Knoxville, who was
sworn in as the President of the Tennessee Association of Criminal Defense Lawyers (TACDL)
in August 2025; and
WHEREAS, the Tennessee Association of Criminal Defense Lawyers was formed and
chartered in 1973, making it the oldest legal defense bar association in the State; TACDL
provides education, training, and support to criminal defense lawyers and advocates for fair and
effective criminal justice in the courts and wherever justice demands; and
WHEREAS, Wade Davies has tried complex cases for more than thirty years,
concentrating on State and federal investigations and criminal trials throughout his career; and
WHEREAS, he has served on the Board of Professional Responsibility of the Supreme
Court of Tennessee and now represents attorneys in matters before the Board; and
WHEREAS, the former President of the Knoxville Bar Association, Mr. Davies is now the
criminal law columnist for the Tennessee Bar Journal and has published over forty columns in
the Journal; and
WHEREAS, his ongoing commitment to his profession resulted in his induction as a
Fellow in the American College of Trial Lawyers in 2016; he currently serves on the College's
Tennessee State Committee and Federal Criminal Procedure Committee; and
SJR0655
012203
- 1 -

WHEREAS, a proud son of the Volunteer State, Mr. Davies graduated first in his class
from the University of Tennessee College of Law in 1993; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Davies's remarkable success inside and outside of the courtroom stems
from his dedication to safeguarding basic human dignity and to serving others with his legal
talents; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Davies has demonstrated the utmost professionalism, ability, and
integrity as an attorney, winning the unbridled respect and admiration of members of the bar
and bench and his community alike; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Wade Davies for his
meritorious service to the people of Tennessee as the 2025-2026 President of the Tennessee
Association of Criminal Defense Lawyers and extend to him our best wishes for every future
success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
